<body lang=EN-GB style='tab-interval:36.0pt'>

<div class=Section1>

<p class=MsoNormal>…It is a patent truth that in every progression the
possibility of regression exists.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>It
was obvious that continuing contact with Barbarians was beginning to teach our
young apprentice a most beneficial respect.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>In retrospect, it was equally obvious that incidents of some kind would
arise whereby Tagelied would be able to feel his accustomed air of
superiority.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>Still, at least when they
did come his more avaricious instincts also received a check...</p>

<p class=MsoNormal><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></p>

<p class=MsoNormal>Master Lutestringer, 37<sup>th</sup> Circle, Historical
section, from his introduction to the compiled travels of Tagelied HalfElven.</p>

<p class=MsoNormal><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><u><span
style='font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt'>The Fifth Report.<o:p></o:p></span></u></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><u><span
style='font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></span></u></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><span style='mso-bidi-font-weight:bold'>Your Graces,<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><span style='mso-bidi-font-weight:bold'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><span style='mso-bidi-font-weight:bold'>I apologise once
again for the long period between reports, but a number of events have
conspired to delay the preparation of the one you are now reading.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><span style='mso-bidi-font-weight:bold'><span
style='mso-tab-count:1'>                </span>Firstly I have been ill.<span
style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>I once again commend Marton Stringsinger for
his diligence and thoroughness.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>He
claimed that there were more drinking songs to be recorded and advised further
investigation of the Taverns in Halas.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>Unfortunately after four more days no songs of any merit had been found
and I was most violently affected by sickness.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>Marton is of the opinion it must have been something I eat.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-indent:36.0pt'><span style='mso-bidi-font-weight:
bold'>Secondly I have been on a hunting trip into the Everfrost plains, a vast
expanse of snow and ice frequented by Orcs, giant spiders and polar bears.<span
style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>Jallt the songwriter had been planning such
an expedition for some time, and I was most pleasantly surprised to be invited
to come.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>I felt that I was making
progress in relating to these extraordinary people, and I found that this was
something that I wished to do.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-indent:36.0pt'><span style='mso-bidi-font-weight:
bold'>At dawn on the appointed day I made my way to Everfrost “ramp”, a
juncture between Halas and the wilds.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>Jallt was already there, but of our other companions there was no
sign.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>Hunting in Everfrost is fraught
with danger at the best of times, and prohibitive at night.<span
style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>I knew that Jallt would not wish to miss a
moment of daylight, and feared that our party would be rent with recrimination
from the very start.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-indent:36.0pt'><span style='mso-bidi-font-weight:
bold'>Nothing could be further from the truth!<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>With admirable pragmatism Jallt simply sat cross-legged on the floor,
pulled out some tatty bear pelts and a tailoring kit, and set to work turning
them into workable garments.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>We chatted
while she worked, and then to my delight she began to sing underneath her
breath, a tune that I knew so very well.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><span style='font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt;
mso-bidi-font-weight:bold'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><u><span
style='font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></span></u></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><u><span
style='font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt'>The Work of the Weavers.<o:p></o:p></span></u></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></p>

<p class=MsoNormal>Accompaniment – Acappella.</p>

<p class=MsoNormal>Pace: Moderato.</p>

<p class=MsoNormal><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></p>

<p class=MsoNormal>Come gather all ye tailors, there’s clothes to be made,</p>

<p class=MsoNormal>With lots of silk thread, and a pelt skinning blade,</p>

<p class=MsoNormal>With needles in our hands we ply the greatest trade,</p>

<p class=MsoNormal>For we’re doing the work of the weavers!</p>

<p class=MsoNormal><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></p>

<p class=MsoNormal>[chorus]</p>

<p class=MsoNormal>If it was’na for the weavers, what would you do?</p>

<p class=MsoNormal>You would’na hae a cloth that's made o’ wool.</p>

<p class=MsoNormal>Ye would’na hae a coat of the black or the blue,</p>

<p class=MsoNormal>If’na it was’na for the work o’ the weavers!</p>

<p class=MsoNormal><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></p>

<p class=MsoNormal>There's the merchants and the freemen, the citizens and all,</p>

<p class=MsoNormal>The bards and magicians, and them outside the law,</p>

<p class=MsoNormal>And folk across the oceans, that no one ever saw,</p>

<p class=MsoNormal>But we know they wear the work of the weavers!</p>

<p class=MsoNormal><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></p>

<p class=MsoNormal>[chorus]</p>

<p class=MsoNormal><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></p>

<p class=MsoNormal>There's our shamans and our warriors - we know that they're
bold</p>

<p class=MsoNormal>But if they did’na hae the clothes, then they could’na live
for cold,</p>

<p class=MsoNormal>The high-born and the lowly, the young and the old,</p>

<p class=MsoNormal>They all want for the work of the weavers!</p>

<p class=MsoNormal><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></p>

<p class=MsoNormal>[chorus]</p>

<p class=MsoNormal><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></p>

<p class=MsoNormal>The tailoring is a trade that never can fail,</p>

<p class=MsoNormal>As long as folk need a cloth to keep themselves hale,</p>

<p class=MsoNormal>So let us al’ be merry o’er a bucket o’ good ale,</p>

<p class=MsoNormal>And we’ll drink a mighty health to the weavers!</p>

<p class=MsoNormal><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></p>

<p class=MsoNormal>(chorus)</p>

<p class=MsoNormal><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></p>

<p class=MsoNormal>I was most gratified to hear this song.<span
style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>As your Graces are certainly aware, it was
the subject of my 4<sup>th</sup> circle summer thesis, an effort rewarded with
a first class certificate and a golden lute award.<span style="mso-spacerun:
yes">  </span>To recap, it is a most popular song and known very well by the
guild.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>It seems to have originated in
the great workshops of Southern Qeynos, but is now widely sung all over western
Antonica.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">   </span>Not surprisingly, there are
innumerable variations on the lyrics and style, and it is quite possible that
there are as many versions as there are tailors!<span style="mso-spacerun:
yes">  </span>This Barbarian effort is full of quaint touches not seen
elsewhere (Shamans rather than Clerics in the third verse for example).<span
style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>Note also the tacit reference to Rogues in
the second - “them outside the law”.</p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-indent:36.0pt'>Jallt patiently sang her version
through three times, while I swiftly scribbled down words and metre.<span
style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>All the time the pelts changed under her
expert hands.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">    </span>By the time I was
satisfied I had the lyric aright she had a beautifully stitched tunic and belt.<span
style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>At that instant a young Barbarian, stripped
to the waist and clutching a very basic sword, came down the Halas ramp and
stared uncertainly into the canyons of snow and ice beyond.<span
style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>Jallt looked him over, and then to my
surprise tossed her newly made garments into his arms.</p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-indent:36.0pt'>“There you gi’, bonnie lad!<span
style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>Na go and gi them goblins what fer!”</p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-indent:36.0pt'>The young man grinned and pulled
the garments on.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>Then with a bow and a
fierce wave of his sword, strode off into Everfrost.<span style="mso-spacerun:
yes">  </span>I stared open-mouthed, for Jallt had not asked for payment for
her possessions, which with her time and hard won skill came to a pretty
penny.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>Truly, the tales of the
generosity of the wolves of the north are not without foundation!</p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-indent:36.0pt'>Jallt decided that we should make
for a waypoint known as “Bandl”.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>Apparently this was a common staging area for forays into the plains,
and she hoped that the others would meet us there.<span style="mso-spacerun:
yes">  </span>We set off straightaway, Jallt seeming to have an instinct for
journeying the twisting canyons, while I kept up with her as best I could.</p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-indent:36.0pt'>The day was bright and clear, but
interminably cold.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>This affects the
body in two adverse and opposite ways.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>On the one hand you become heavily sunburnt.<span style="mso-spacerun:
yes">  </span>On the other a chill seeps into your very bones.<span
style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>We saw many Barbarians who did not have the
benefit of even patched garments, and I did not envy their state of undress in
this harsh climate.</p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-indent:36.0pt'>Bandl turned out to be a person,
not a place.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>A guard of the wolves of
the north, he was surrounded by folk of diverse races, all preparing to move
eastwards onto the plains.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>Barbarians
dominated.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>Jallt found one of the
warriors who had agreed to come with us, and made the acquaintance of two
shamans, so that we were five strong, a good size.<span style="mso-spacerun:
yes">  </span>The newcomers regarded me suspiciously, but upon Jallt vouching
for my integrity, they all clasped my hand and swore to be as brothers for the
duration of the expedition.</p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-indent:36.0pt'>The warriors took the lead, with
the shamans backing them up and myself in the rear.<span style="mso-spacerun:
yes">  </span>We made good progress, the snow and ice being too thin to hinder
rapid movement.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>Several polar bears
fell swift victim to our concerted attacks, but Jallt was after bigger
game.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>She intended to hunt mammoth.</p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-indent:36.0pt'>I shall never forget my first
sight of these magnificent creatures, which graze slowly over the tundra in
majestic unconcern, confident in the protective powers of their thick, hairy
hides.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>I confess I was much alarmed at
the prospect of facing one, but Jallt laughed and assured me that our target
would be a calf, which would be challenge enough.<span style="mso-spacerun:
yes">  </span>After an hour, we found a likely target and Jallt deployed us in
a half moon ambush position.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>She then
attacked the giant and ran, leading it onto the rest of us.<span
style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>She did not delay.<span style="mso-spacerun:
yes">  </span>For such a large creature the mammoth has a surprising turn of
speed.</p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-indent:36.0pt'>The hunting party then surrounded
the beast and took turns to assault it, dividing its frenzied counterattacks.<span
style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>It eventually succumbed, but only after all
of us had felt buffets from its powerful tusks.<span style="mso-spacerun:
yes">  </span>It was a most exhilarating experience, and lucrative too, for
both ivory and meat are of great value.</p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-indent:36.0pt'>We decided to rest and recover
from our exertions, but unfortunately while we had been hunting mammoth, we
were ourselves being hunted.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>No sooner
had we sat than an Orc appeared from behind a ridge and neatly decapitated one
of the Shamans.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>With a curse, Jallt
leapt up and took revenge upon the greenskin.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>As she stood over its lifeless body, I saw her surrounded by a blue
shimmer and then stagger with the force of an ice spell.<span
style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>Two more Orcs charged up, one of them weaving
his arms in a manner that bespoke evil magic.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>Our remaining Shaman countered as best he could with healing magic, but
the Orcs were too strong for our enfeebled state.<span style="mso-spacerun:
yes">  </span>Jallt gave the pre-arranged signal to retreat, all the time
battling with her great two-handed sword against the foul creatures.<span
style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>There followed a running battle over the
snow.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>All sense of time and direction
was lost.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>Eventually, praise Rodcet,
our enemies were defeated, but not before we had lost the second Shaman.</p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-indent:36.0pt'>We were now much the worse for
wear, fatigued and injured, and a long way from safety.<span
style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>Night had fallen swiftly while we were
preoccupied, as it does in the Northlands, and the unending expanse of snow and
ice gave no clue as to our location.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>Our lanterns failed to pierce the dark for more than a few steps.<span
style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>The faces of both my Barbarian companions
were filled with concern.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>Jallt
explained that all manner of evil roamed the plains at night, but the creature
she feared most was the snow leopard, a most aggressive and tenacious predator
that had no fear of Man, Elf or Barbarian.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>It seemed we might very well die here, and our bodies be lost and
forgotten.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-indent:36.0pt'>We huddled together in the cold
and the dark, shared our meagre rations, and prayed for morning. The night
seemed interminable, and the loneliness oppressing.<span style="mso-spacerun:
yes">  </span>I volunteered to give us cheer with a song, but Jallt forbade it,
fearing such sound would bring our enemies down upon us.<span
style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>The long howls of wolves and other, worse,
monsters filled the night air.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>At times
the howls seemed to come closer, but then they would fade away again.<span
style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>Jallt explained that the wolf has a trick of
throwing its voice so that it becomes impossible to locate.<span
style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>On several occasions one or other of us
glimpsed movement in the gloom, and twice we had to scurry away from roving
bands of Orcs.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><span style='mso-tab-count:1'>                </span>On the
second occasion we had just got clear when Jallt’s worst fear came true.<span
style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>A large dappled cat leapt out in front of us
and pounced on the unfortunate warrior who was our third companion.<span
style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>In our enfeebled state it was more than a
match for all of us.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>He bravely shouted
for us to escape while he held it off, but we disdained from abandoning
him.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>Whereupon he backed off into the
night, leading the fell beast on, and calling for us to remember him to his
family and to uphold his name with honor.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>I still demurred, but Jallt dragged me away in the opposite direction,
exclaiming that the warrior had chosen his fate and we would do wrong by
denying his sacrifice.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>Thus we escaped.</p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-indent:36.0pt'>The name of the hero was
Trishder.</p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-indent:36.0pt'>Our situation was still parlous,
for we were now hopelessly lost and there was still no sign of this terrible
night coming to an end.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>The hunt had
turned sour, as indeed it ever is when you are the hunted and not the
hunter.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>We were reduced to cowering in
hollows and behind rocks, bandaging our injuries as best we might, and hoping
that the next sound was not Orcs come to murder us.</p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-indent:36.0pt'>But the sound we did hear was the
call of a peewitt, a repetitious swooping melody, called to greet the dawn, and
acting as the herald of our salvation.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>I tell you true, of all the songs of the north I had heard, this was the
sweetest.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>We rose and saw the new day,
and as the gloom retreated, in the distance the light burnt by the faithful
guard Bandl.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>Soon we were back in
Halas, with warmth and good beer beckoning.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>However, even though she could barely stand with injury and fatigue,
Jallt first sought out the hero’s family and presented them with all the gold
she had made on the expedition.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>I was
humbled, and did the same.</p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-indent:36.0pt'><span style='mso-bidi-font-weight:
bold'>It seems strange to me that I have been on this Barbarian song recording
expedition for nearly five weeks.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>It
seems years, and yet it also seems to have gone by so very swiftly.<span
style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>Whereas I once held this appointment with
much contempt, I now see that beneath their facade of ignorance and grinding
practicality, there is a deep and decidedly spiritual aspect to these Northern
folk.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>They are harsh and unmerciful to
their enemies, but also generous and unswerving to those they count as
friends.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>I shall miss being here.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><span style='mso-bidi-font-weight:bold'><span
style='mso-tab-count:1'>                </span>For, this is the final report I
shall post.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>I head back to Qeynos in
two days time, and shall deliver an account of that period and my homeward
journey by hand.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>Please pass the news
of my return to those I count my friends, and be sure that I shall bring them
all gifts.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></p>

<p class=MsoNormal>Written this day by my hand,</p>

<p class=MsoNormal><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></p>

<p class=MsoNormal>Tagelied HalfElven, of the 6<sup>th</sup> Circle, Antonican
league of Bards.</p>

<p class=MsoNormal><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></p>

<p class=MsoNormal>(You can find both Tagelied and Jallt on the Tholuxe Paells
server).</p>

<p class=MsoNormal><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></p>

</div>

